The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Budget carrier GoAir has announced free tickets for children up to 12 years during the summer vacations. The offer opened Monday and passengers can book free tickets till April 20.          
	ce summer vacation travel is a family phenomenon, we are enabling more families to travel with their kids without impacting their budgetary allocation, said Edgardo Badiali, CEO of GoAir.                            
	 Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) has signed a five-year, multi-million dollar contract with ArvinMeritor. As part of the contract, TCS will set up a centre in Pune that will provide engineering services to ArvinMeritor, with focus on the Asian market.                             
	 Durgapur Steel Plant (DSP) has crossed rated capacity production in hot metal, crude steel and saleable steel, which stood at 2.19, 1.91 and 1.72 million tonnes, respectively, in the financial year 2007-08.                             
	 Kotak Life Insurance has posted a growth rate of 88 per cent for the year ended March 31, 2008. The adjusted premium equivalent has grown to Rs 1,052 crore from Rs 559 crore in the previous fiscal. Its total received premium grew to Rs 1,691 crore from Rs 972 crore.                             
	 Subhash Projects and Marketing Ltd (SPML) has bagged the Bongaigaon thermal power project worth Rs 329.48 crore from National Thermal Power Corporation.                             
	 Yahoo India has introduced maps in 9 local Indian languages along with walking directions. The service is available on the Yahoo! India maps. Accessible via e-mail, SMS and the web, the service offers displays of prominent landmarks, ATMs, petrol pumps, restaurants and hotels.                            
	 Vodafone Essar has opened two stores in Calcutta. The stores are located at Camac Street and the South City Mall. Apart from the availability of new connections and handsets, the stores will offer other value-added services.                            
	 Samsung DSLR and NV cameras have received an approval from Russias Energia as outer space digital camera provider. The cameras will be used to record the daily life in space for 10 days during which their capabilities will also be tested.                             
	 Spaces Home amp; Beyond has unveiled its summer collection for 2008, called the Colour X Change, in Mumbai. Priced at Rs 6,995, the collection is available in four selections.                            
	 Regenix Drugs has launched an electronic infrared thermometer called ThermoFlash LX-26. The product is priced at Rs 6,000 and comes with a 2-year warranty.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
